file or simply cut off in the source I received. I'm noticing the source material claims four examples will be shown but only three appear in what's been provided to me—the fourth example about external interfaces seems to be missing from the truncated source. Rather than speculate about what might come after, I should focus on what I can actually verify: there's a definite gap between what the documentation promises and what's present in the knowledge file. I'm identifying the key omission: the knowledge file is missing the explicit note that domain definition, validation processing definition, and data type definition configurations share the same settings as the message design loader, which the source document clearly states should be noted for brevity.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22940,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":22940,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"72f0ec5e-0bed-4dea-82e9-c35b039aff01","uuid":"028b727a-d6fd-439a-97e1-3d420af21a04"}
